<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 13 at 7:34PM CDT until June 14 at 12:00AM CDT by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 800 PM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN MCCURTAIN COUNTY...
At 734 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 11 miles southeast
of Idabel, or 16 miles west of Foreman, moving east at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Haworth, Bokhoma, Tom, Moon, America, Harris, Goodwater and
Shinewell.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>This storm is producing large hail. SEEK SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy
structure and stay away from windows.</instruction>
